    <h1>Kloud Standard Token (KST) Documentation</h1>

    <section>
        <h2>Purpose</h2>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Transaction Facilitation:</strong> KST facilitates transactions and covers fees within the Kloudspace Hub platform.</li>
            <li><strong>Fee Coverage:</strong> It covers fees for minting DST20 tokens and NFTs.</li>
            <li><strong>Inter-Chain Bridge:</strong> Enables seamless transactions across various blockchain networks, including Polygon.</li>
        </ul>
    </section>

    <section>
        <h2>Key Features</h2>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>DST20 Compliance:</strong> Ensures compatibility and security within the DeFichains ecosystem.</li>
            <li><strong>Layer 2 Protocol:</strong> Operates efficiently with reduced costs and increased scalability.</li>
            <li><strong>Multi-Chain Compatibility:</strong> Works across various blockchain networks, notably Polygon.</li>
        </ul>
    </section>

    <section>
        <h2>Use Cases</h2>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Transaction Payments:</strong> Used to pay for services, products, or transactions.</li>
            <li><strong>Token Creation:</strong> Covers fees for minting new tokens and NFTs.</li>
            <li><strong>Cross-Chain Transactions:</strong> Facilitates smooth asset transfers across different chains.</li>
        </ul>
    </section>

    <section>
        <h2>Future Developments</h2>
        <p>The development team aims to enhance utility, scalability, and interoperability for KST.</p>
    </section>

    <section>
        <h2>Conclusion</h2>
        <p>Kloud Standard Token (KST) is a fundamental element within Kloudspace Hub, facilitating transactions, covering fees, enabling token creation, and promoting cross-chain interoperability.</p>
    </section>

